<Page xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      Title="The Stylus Tool Dialog">
    <FlowDocumentReader ViewingMode="Scroll">
        <FlowDocument>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"
                       FontSize="16pt">
                The Stylus Tool Dialog
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Stylus Tool</Bold> dialog lets you change the 
                dimensions, shape, and color of the stylus, and other
                aspects of its behavior.
            </Paragraph>
            <BlockUIContainer>
                <Image Source="StylusToolDialog.png" 
                       Stretch="None"/>
            </BlockUIContainer>
            <Paragraph>
                Use the <Bold>Width</Bold> and <Bold>Height</Bold> fields
                to specify the dimensions of the stylus in points
                (1/72<Run BaselineAlignment="Superscript">nd</Run> inch).
                You can use different horizontal and vertical dimensions
                for calligraphic effects.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Use the <Bold>Rotation</Bold> field to specify a 
                rotation of the stylus tip. The rotation only makes sense
                when the horizontal and vertical dimensions of the stylus
                are unequal.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The stylus tip can be either elliptical or rectangular.
                Pick the shape you want.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                When you check the <Bold>Ignore Pressure</Bold> item,
                the pressure of the stylus on the screen has no effect
                on the width of the lines you draw. Checking this option
                has no effect if you're drawing ink with the mouse.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                When you check the <Bold>Highlighter</Bold> item,
                the lines are drawn with 50% transparency.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Choose the color you want from the list box.
            </Paragraph>
        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentReader>
</Page>

